---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About" description="About Matt Galvin — designer and developer.">
  <div style="padding-top: 10rem; padding-bottom: 4rem; padding-left: 2.5rem; padding-right: 2.5rem; max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto;">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="anim-1" style="margin-bottom: 5rem;">
      <p style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a8076; margin-bottom: 1rem;">About</p>
      <h1 class="font-display" style="font-size: clamp(3rem, 9vw, 9rem); font-weight: 300; line-height: 0.9; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
        Nice to<br />
        <em style="font-style: italic; color: #b5421a;">meet you.</em>
      </h1>
    </div>
<div class="anim-2" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6rem; border-top: 1px solid #ccc5b8; padding-top: 4rem;">

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.2fr; gap: 6rem; align-items: start;">
    
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem;">
      <p class="font-display" style="font-size: 1.4rem; line-height: 1.3; color: #1a1612;">
        I taught Cast Members how to create the best experiences in the world.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; font-weight: 300; color: #3d3830;">
        I taught Cast Members at <strong>The Walt Disney Company</strong> how to create the best experiences in the world. From those parks to the consumer frontline of <strong>Vodafone</strong>, I’ve spent my career bridging the gap between our clients and our technical execution. Currently, I lead that mission at <strong>Luxury Presence</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; padding-top: 0.4rem;">
      <p style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a8076;">Professional History</p>
      <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
        {[
          { name: "Luxury Presence", role: "Manager, Client Support" },
          { name: "ecobee", role: "Senior Support Specialist" },
          { name: "The Walt Disney Company", role: "Trainer, Cast Member" },
          { name: "Vodafone", role: "Customer Operations" }
        ].map((job) => (
          <li style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0eee9; padding-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-weight: 500; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #1a1612;">{job.name}</span>
            <span style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; color: #8a8076; text-transform: uppercase;">{job.role}</span>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.2fr; gap: 6rem; align-items: start;">
    
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem;">
      <p class="font-display" style="font-size: 1.4rem; line-height: 1.3; color: #1a1612;">
        Architecting a transition into Product.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; font-weight: 300; color: #3d3830;">
        My current focus is a rigorous period of professional development to bridge the gap between leadership and product strategy. I’m combining formal certifications with hands-on tinkering to master the space where user needs meet technical architecture.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; padding-top: 0.4rem;">
      <p style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a8076;">Active Arsenal</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem;">
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;">
           <li style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; color: #b5421a; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">[ IN PROGRESS ]</li>
           <li style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #1a1612; border-left: 1px solid #f0eee9; padding-left: 0.75rem;">Google PM Pro</li>
           <li style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #1a1612; border-left: 1px solid #f0eee9; padding-left: 0.75rem;">Scrum.org PSPO I</li>
        </ul>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;">
           <li style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; color: #8a8076; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">[ VALIDATED ]</li>
           <li style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #1a1612; border-left: 1px solid #f0eee9; padding-left: 0.75rem;">AWS AI Practitioner</li>
           <li style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #1a1612; border-left: 1px solid #f0eee9; padding-left: 0.75rem;">Google People Mgmt</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
    <!-- Two-column content -->
    <div class="anim-2" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 6rem; align-items: start; border-top: 1px solid #ccc5b8; padding-top: 4rem;">

      <!-- Left: photo placeholder -->
      <div>
        <div style="aspect-ratio: 3/4; background: #e6e0d4; display: flex; align-items: end; justify-content: start; padding: 1.5rem; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
          <!-- Decorative texture -->
          <div style="position: absolute; inset: 0; background: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, transparent, transparent 2px, rgba(0,0,0,0.015) 2px, rgba(0,0,0,0.015) 4px);"></div>
          <span style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a8076; position: relative; z-index: 1;">Photo coming soon</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: bio -->
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem; padding-top: 1rem;">
        
        <p class="font-display" style="font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: #1a1612;">
          I'm Matt — a designer and developer who cares deeply about craft, clarity, and the space between the two.
        </p>

        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; font-weight: 300; color: #3d3830;">
          <p>
          I’ve spent my career navigating complex digital ecosystems at scale. Currently, I lead Advanced Support at Luxury Presence, bridging the gap between high-value real estate clients and our product teams. Before that, I spent time at The Walt Disney Company teaching new Cast Members how to create the best experiences in the world, and at ecobee, where I dove deep into the intersection of IoT and smart home energy. My foundation was built in the fast-paced consumer operations world at Vodafone.
          </p>
          <p>
            Right now I'm focused on [what you're focused on]. Previously I worked at [past companies or projects]. Before that, [whatever came before].
          </p>
          <div style="border-top: 1px solid #ccc5b8; padding-top: 2.5rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
  <p style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a8076; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    Professional Development & Certifications
  </p>
  
  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem;">
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
      <p style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.55rem; color: #b5421a; text-transform: uppercase;">In Progress</p>
      <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;">
        <li style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #1a1612; border-left: 2px solid #f0eee9; padding-left: 1rem;">
          Google Project Management Professional
        </li>
        <li style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #1a1612; border-left: 2px solid #f0eee9; padding-left: 1rem;">
          PSPO I — Scrum.org
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
      <p style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.55rem; color: #8a8076; text-transform: uppercase;">Validated</p>
      <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;">
        <li style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #1a1612; border-left: 2px solid #f0eee9; padding-left: 1rem;">
          AWS Certified AI Practitioner
        </li>
        <li style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #1a1612; border-left: 2px solid #f0eee9; padding-left: 1rem;">
          Google People Management
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
          <p>
            Outside of work, you'll find me [hobbies, interests, things that make you a human].
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Skills/stack -->
        <div style="padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid #ccc5b8;">
          <p style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a8076; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Currently working with</p>
          <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem;">
            {["TypeScript", "React", "Astro", "Go", "Postgres", "Tailwind", "Cloudflare"].map((s) => (
              <span style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 0.3rem 0.7rem; border: 1px solid #ccc5b8; color: #8a8076;">{s}</span>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Links -->
        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; padding-top: 0.5rem;">
          <a href="https://github.com/mglvn" class="link-arrow" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            GitHub ↗
          </a>
          <a href="mailto:hello@mattgalvin.dev" class="link-arrow">
            hello@mattgalvin.dev →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
